<div id="review_4004605283" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4004605283" />
    <a title="Kristina Rasmussen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10636325-kristina-rasmussen"><img alt="Kristina Rasmussen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1519751503p2/10636325.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4004605283?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kristina Rasmussen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kristina Rasmussen" href="/user/show/10636325-kristina-rasmussen">Kristina Rasmussen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781573454063" href="/book/show/433160.Far_From_Home">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4004605283" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6103381719321961274">These books are HEAVY. I feel like I’m changing as I read them. People often talk about how reading lets you experience life in ways you wouldn’t otherwise and widens your world. This series has done that for me. I wonder how I might have handled these situations and feel immense gratitude that I didn’t have to. I’m ready for “this war” to end and to see what happens to the Thomas family. But I may need to give myself a little time before I finish reading volumes 4 and 5. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


